</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[766,1352,643,1069]" pageId="16" pageNumber="635">
Some authors consider 
<taxonomicName box="[1106,1239,730,755]" class="Mammalia" family="Mustelidae" genus="Melogale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="16" pageNumber="635" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="everetii">M. everetii</taxonomicName>
and/or 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Horsfield" baseAuthorityYear="1821" box="[769,884,761,794]" class="Mammalia" family="Mustelidae" genus="Melogale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="16" pageNumber="635" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="orientalis">orientalis</taxonomicName>
as conspecific with M. personata. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[766,1097,840,873]" pageId="16" pageNumber="635" type="distribution">
